<br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">Skeptic</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:white;">Humanist</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">Naturalist</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
Atheist<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">Bright</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:white;">Secularist</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">Darwinist</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
There are many names.  I personally believe in the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>TRUTH</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  It really bugs me when people run off and claim they have the truth or their beliefs are the truth, but they cannot support it with fact or evidence.  The <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>TRUTH</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is supported by logic and reason, otherwise it isn't really <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>True</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Anyway, the point to this post is yet another movement to repaint atheism/naturalism/reason is underway.  That <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">red</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> one up there near the middle, <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.the-brights.net/" target="top">Bright</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> is the latest attempt to break away from the stigma associated with using reason and intelligence to see the world rather than dogma and rote.  Check it out if you are interested in another name to call yourself.  <br>
<br>
(If someone could post this on the A/A board at BC too please?)<br>
 <p>DBC67<br>
