<br>
Sure, we can drill down from there to positive/negative atheists vs. agnostics who say whether god exists is unknowable or at least his nature is, but in the end if you don't hold faith in go, you're an atheist and if you do you're a theist. The word is very simple and should stand. Humanist, naturalist and Darwinist all imply another belief or set of them in addition to atheism. Whether these usually accompany it is another issue, but certainly no cause to change the word atheism itself. <br>
<br>
Bright....truth....eep! JW's and many Catholics I know refer to their religion as &quot;the truth&quot; too so connotations already exist which the Bright group seems not to appreciate. What a bunch of yahoos!!<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Maybe instead of forming this group energy would be better spent attempting to change the false perceptions about atheists and what atheism is rather than mislabelling themselves.<br>
