Edited to add: please doctor logic, provide us with a syllogism thast proves the non-existence of anything.  She has made a positive assertion, that requires evidence.  The more extreme the claim, the more demanding the evidence required to substantiate it.  My making of the assertion for non-existence cannot be proven aside form application of Ockham's Razor or the disproof of affirmative qualities she claims.  We have an invisible talking pink air-breathing telepathic etherial carp that dwells around here for these types of discussions.  Please disprove him. <p>DBC67<br>
