Finally.  You seem to have a slightly skewed view of atheism.  Whether he/she/they is/are recognized as god(s) or not, if any god(s) exist(s) then atheism is shown to be wrong.  This means that the probability of atheism being wrong is equal to y = 1- the product of x<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;">i</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> where x is the probability that thing i is not a deity, and the set that makes up i is everything in the universe.  This is also the equation for something in the universe qualifying as god.  Since you said that there are effectively an infinite number of things in the universe that could be gods, i is a set which is infinitely large.  For argument sake, let’s say that the probability of being god for each thing is the same.  This changes the equation to y = 1 – x^n where n is the total number of things in set i.  Since you put it forward, we will use the probability of the things being god shall be taken as you said to be near zero.  This makes the probability of it not being god near one, yet slightly below one.  As n approaches infinity for x^n, any value of x between 0 and 1 will result in a value of near 0 for the evaluated exponential.(basic exponential mathematics)  This results in the probability of atheism being wrong to be near 1 or in percentage, near 100%.<br>
